title.narrative: By 2021, disaggregated data from surveys and administrative data available to inform policy, planning and monitoring

description.narrative: UNICEF supported further analysis of LSIS-II data and the dissemination of results. Several secondary analyses were carried out in 2019, including a nutrition/stunting analysis, immunization analysis, and education analysis. To inform the MTR of the current Country Programme an in-depth Situation Analysis was carried out. Efforts were made to strengthen routine administrative data systems at sub-national level to generate more frequent data for monitoring results for children. The EU-UNICEF supported National Information Platform for Nutrition has consolidated nutrition-related data from relevant sectors to support the development of evidence-based policies and programmes, to build national capacity on data and policy analysis. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:18/02/2020
